--- G/Model Choice
+++ D1/Model Choice
@@ -1 +1 @@
-A stiffness-aware PINN: fully connected MLP mapping (x,t) to u, 4 hidden layers of 128 units, tanh, with random Fourier features on the inputs (64 features, sigma = 5) so the network can represent the high-frequency content of sharp interfaces; a periodic input embedding (harmonics k = 1..4 in x) makes the representation exactly periodic in value and derivative. Alternatives: SIREN or other spectral networks, domain-decomposition PINNs, or adaptive-sampling PINNs - a shallow plain-tanh network cannot resolve the interfaces.
