--- G/Validation Failure Risks
+++ D1/Validation Failure Risks
@@ -1 +1 @@
-Compare against a spectral or adaptive high-fidelity numerical reference; report the PDE residual error, the interface location / phase classification error over time (not only a global MSE), the periodicity error in value and derivative, and the sensitivity of the result to sampling density. Failure risks: (1) ignoring stiffness, so training collapses to a trivial smooth solution; (2) omitting the double-well term u - u^3, i.e. treating the problem as pure diffusion; (3) enforcing only value periodicity; (4) a network without high-frequency capacity (shallow plain tanh) that cannot resolve sharp interfaces; (5) under-sampling near the interfaces - mitigated by RAR and monitored via the interface error.
